abilities.effect:
You're made of earth and stone, granting you the durability of the earth and resistance against most forms of harm. However, you cannot swim, and are incredibly heavy for your size.
&nbsp;
When your earthen form would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction; alternatively, when it would be a hindrance, lose a die.

You're made of flickering flames, making you one of the most destructive spirits and a reliable form of heat. However, you cannot swim and water is incredibly deadly to you.
&nbsp;
When your flame form would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction; alternatively, when it would be a hindrance, lose a die.

You're made of metal, which makes you immune to many of the normal hazards of the world and grants exceptional toughness.
&nbsp;
When your metallic form would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You're made of wind, which allows you to fly easily and readily, makes you difficult to see, completely amorphous, and, unlike other spirits, makes it almost impossible to suppress your presence.
&nbsp;
When your wind form or ability to fly would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You're made of wood and plantlife, granting you hardiness and the ability to grow with your environment.
&nbsp;
When your wooden form would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

This creature has a natural sense of balance and is incredibly stable on their feet, allowing them to fit on surfaces that should be far to small for them.
&nbsp;
When their balance or stability would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You are covered in small blooms and plant growths, and can sustain some small number of plants no matter the climate. These plants are typically not particularly potent on their own, but plants near you seem to grow faster and healthier than they normally would.
&nbsp;
When your living plant-like nature would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You are capable of creating thin threads made of metal that are exceptionally strong and can be fired a short distance. This can be used as rope, thread, or a variety of other potential uses. At GM's discretion, after using too much of this Ability, you may be required to rest and recover it as if it was _Fatigue_.
&nbsp;
When your threads would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You have natural appendages or aptitude for climbing, and can easily climb all but the most sheer or difficult of surfaces effortlessly.
&nbsp;
When your ability to climb would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You have a keen sense of smell, which allows you to notice things other might miss as well as track other creatures.
&nbsp;
When your sense of smell would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You excel at hunting other creatures and eliminating them; you have keen senses, a natural sense of stealth, and are intimidating to most other natural creatures.
&nbsp;
When your talents as a predator would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You are a creature accustomed to functioning in a pack, and have an innate sense of the natural hierarchy of things, and tend to fit in well in human society.
&nbsp;
When your nature as a pack animal would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You are a cute creature, causing others to feel a natural affection towards you and comforted in your presence.
&nbsp;
When your cuteness would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You are naturally stealthy and able to hide your presence with ease. Your steps make no sound and, when you try to, you can move through tall grass or similar without a trace. Creatures without specialized or enhanced senses will always fail to find you when you try to hide.
&nbsp;
When your stealth would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction. Additionally, in these circumstances you may spend one [ ] as if it were [-] or to play *Subtlety* if appropriate.

You can channel incredible bursts of speed, allowing you to rapidly cover ground and outrun nearly every creature so long as you're moving in a straight line.
&nbsp;
When your raw speed would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You have a natural shepherding instinct, causing other animals to trust you and giving you an instinctive protective response to danger.
&nbsp;
When your protective nature and watchfulness would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You are quick on your feet and more nimble than most. In matters of speed and agility, you almost always win.
&nbsp;
When your speed and agility would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction. Additionally, in these circumstances you may spend one [ ] as if it were [-] or to play *Speed* if appropriate.

You are extremely small, somewhere between the size of a rat and a typical cat, granting you greatly improved agility and speed.
&nbsp;
When your tiny size would aid or harm a situation, gain or lose +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You are small, somewhere between the size of a cat and typical dog, granting you increased agility and speed.
&nbsp;
When your small size would aid or harm a situation, gain or lose +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You are somewhere between the size of a typical dog and a human
&nbsp;
Your size neither harms nor helps Skill Challenges and Interactions.

You are somewhere between the size of a human and a horse, granting you increased strength and power.
&nbsp;
When your large size would aid or harm a situation, gain or lose +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.
